'''Malik Leon Tillman''' (born May 28, 2002) is a professional [[Association football|soccer]] player who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for {{German football updater|BaLeverk}} club [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]]. Born in Germany, he represents the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States national team]].

Tillman is a graduate of [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]]'s youth system, which he joined in 2015 from [[SpVgg Greuther Fürth|Greuther Fürth]]. He made his debut for Bayern's first-team in August 2021, having previously featured for [[FC Bayern Munich II|Bayern Munich II]]. In July 2022, he signed for [[Scottish Premiership]] club [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] on loan, where he won the [[PFA Scotland Young Player of the Year]] award for the [[2022–23 in Scottish football|2022–23]] season. In August 2023, he went on loan to [[Eredivisie]] club [[PSV Eindhoven]] and won the league in [[2023–24 Eredivisie|2023–24]], with the club permanently signing him in May 2024, winning the league again in [[2024–25 Eredivisie|2024–25]]. In July 2025, Tillman signed a five-year contract to Bundesliga club Bayer Leverkusen for $41 million.

Tillman represented both his country of birth, Germany, and the United States at youth international level. He made his senior international debut for the United States in June 2022.

== Club career ==
=== Bayern Munich ===
Born in [[Nuremberg]], Tillman was part of the youth squad at [[SpVgg Greuther Fürth|Greuther Fürth]] before joining [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] along with his brother [[Timothy Tillman]] in 2015.<ref name="Tillman">{{cite news |title=Justin Butler, Chris Richards, and the nascent US stars earning their stripes at Bayern Munich |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayern-munich-s-young-americans-butler-richards-booth-tillman-usa-usmnt-3711 |accessdate=June 10, 2020 |work=Bundesliga}}</ref> He was quickly promoted to the under-19 squad after putting in good performances for the under-17s.<ref name="Tillman"/>

Tillman made his professional debut on June 9, 2020, when he came on as a substitute for [[FC Bayern Munich II|Bayern Munich II]], the club's reserve side, against [[FSV Zwickau|Zwickau]]. He started and played 57 minutes as Bayern Munich II won 2–0.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bayern Munich 2-0 Zwickau |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2020/06/09/germany/3-liga/fc-bayern-munchen-ii/fsv-zwickau/3053438/ |website=Soccerway}}</ref>

He was promoted to Bayern Munich's senior team during the first round of the [[2021–22 DFB-Pokal]] against [[Bremer SV]] on August 25, 2021. He came on as a substitute at the start of the second half and scored a goal in the 12–0 victory.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://7news.com.au/sport/soccer/bayern-munich-win-12-0-in-german-cup-rout-c-3782743 |title=Bayern Munich win 12-0 in German Cup rout |website=7news.com.au |date=August 25, 2021 |access-date=December 17, 2022}}</ref>

He made his [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut on December 8, 2021, coming on as a substitute late in the second half against [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/matches/profis/champions-league/2021-2022/fc-bayern-muenchen-fc-barcelona-08-12-2021/report |title=Blistering Reds down Barca |publisher=FC Bayern Munich |date=December 8, 2021 }}</ref>

==== Loan to Rangers ====
[[File:Malik Tillman 2022.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Tillman with [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] in 2022.]]

On July 15, 2022, Tillman joined Scottish club [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] on a season long loan, with the club having an exclusive option to buy.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Rangers Sign Malik Tillman From Bayern Munich |url=https://www.rangers.co.uk/Article/rangers-sign-malik-tillman-from-bayern-munich/RzOQJYPLQs6hEaZSKnfa9 |access-date=July 15, 2022 |website=rangers.co.uk}}</ref> He made his debut for the club against [[Scottish Premiership]] side [[Livingston F.C.|Livingston]], as a second-half substitute, during a 2–1 win on July 30.<ref>{{ cite news | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62275140 | title=Livingston 1-2 Rangers | work=BBC Sport | date=July 30, 2022 }}</ref> He scored his first goal for Rangers in a [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] qualifier against Belgian side [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise|Union Saint-Gilloise]] on August 9,<ref>{{ cite news | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62460304  | title=Rangers 3-0 Union Saint-Gilloise| work=BBC Sport | date=August 10, 2022 }}</ref> and followed this by netting the opening goal in a 4–0 league victory at home over [[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]] three days later.<ref>{{ cite news | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62445663  | title=Rangers 4-0 St Johnstone| work=BBC Sport | date=August 13, 2022 }}</ref>

=== PSV ===
On August 10, 2023, Tillman extended his contract with Bayern Munich until 2026.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/de/news/2023/08/spielpraxis-in-eindhoven-fc-bayern-verlaengert-vertrag-mit-malik-tillman |title=FC Bayern verlängert Vertrag mit Malik Tillman |publisher=FC Bayern Munich |language=de |date=August 10, 2023 }}</ref> On the same day, he joined [[Eredivisie]] club [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] on loan with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.psv.nl/nieuwspagina/artikel/transfer-psv-versterkt-middenveld-met-malik-tillman-.htm |title=Transfer {{!}} PSV versterkt middenveld met Malik Tillman |publisher=PSV |language=nl |date=August 10, 2023 }}</ref> On September 2, he scored his first goal on his Eredivisie debut in a 4–0 away win over [[RKC Waalwijk|Waalwijk]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/usmnt-ricardo-pepi-malik-tillman-sergino-dest-psv/bltcd37bde723c45b12 |title=Malik Tillman scores off bench for PSV as USMNT stars Sergino Dest and Ricardo Pepi feature in lopsided win over RKC Waalwijk |publisher=Goal.com |date=September 2, 2023 }}</ref> On October 3, he provided his first Champions League assist in a 2–2 draw with [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sbisoccer.com/2023/10/malik-tillman-makes-impact-in-psvs-ucl-draw-with-sevilla |title=Malik Tillman makes impact in PSV's UCL draw with Sevilla |publisher=SBI Soccer |date=October 3, 2023 }}</ref>

On May 10, 2024, PSV opted to activate the buy option, securing Tillman's transfer permanently by finalizing a contract extending until 2028.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.psv.nl/media/artikel/transfer-malik-tillman-tekent-tot-medio-2028-bij-psv |title=Transfer {{!}} Malik Tillman tekent tot medio 2028 bij PSV |publisher=PSV |language=nl |date=May 10, 2024 }}</ref> The transfer fee was reportedly €12 million, with a buyback clause to Bayern of approximately €35 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tribuna.com/de/news/fcbayern-2024-05-11-so-viel-geld-musste-fc-bayern-zahlen-um-malik-tillman-zuruckzuholen-topquelle/ |title=So viel Geld müsste FC Bayern zahlen, um Malik Tillman zurückzuholen - Top-Quelle|trans-title=That's how much money FC Bayern would have to pay to bring Malik Tillman back - top source |publisher=Tribuna.com |language=de |date=May 11, 2024 }}</ref>

=== Bayer Leverkusen ===
[[File:Malik-Tillman-2025.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Tillman with [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] in 2025.]]

On July 12, 2025, Tillman joined [[Bundesliga]] side [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] on a five-year deal after the club made a bid reported to be €35 million, representing a club record fee for Leverkusen alongside [[Jarell Quansah]]'s move to the German club, as well as the second-highest [[List of most expensive American soccer transfers|American soccer transfer]] of all-time.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/usa-international-malik-tillman-joins-bayer-04-from-psv |title=USA international Malik Tillman joins Bayer 04 from PSV |publisher=Bayer 04 Leverkusen |date=July 12, 2025 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6445200/2025/07/12/malik-tillman-transfer-leverkusen/ |title=Bayer Leverkusen complete deal to sign USMNT's Malik Tillman from PSV Eindhoven |publisher=The Athletic |date=July 12, 2025 }}</ref> On August 30, Tillman scored on his debut with the club, a 3–3 league draw to [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Stafford-Bloor |first=Sebastian |date=2025-08-30 |title=USMNT's Malik Tillman scores in a Leverkusen debut marred by blown lead |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6586186/2025/08/30/malik-tillman-goal-bayer-leverkusen-debut-usmnt/ |access-date=2025-08-31 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

== International career ==
[[File:Malik Tillman, 2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup, 01.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Tillman playing for the United States at the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].]]

Tillman was initially eligible to represent both [[Germany national football team|Germany]], his birth nation, and the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]], through his father.<ref name="Tillman"/> He played youth international soccer for the United States at [[United States boys' national under-15 soccer team|under-15]] level<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sbisoccer.com/2022/05/bayern-munich-prospect-malik-tillman-to-play-for-the-usmnt |title=Bayern Munich prospect Malik Tillman to play for the USMNT |website=sbisoccer.com |date=May 19, 2022 |access-date=December 17, 2022}}</ref> and Germany at [[Germany national under-15 football team|under-15]], [[Germany national under-16 football team|under-16]], [[Germany national under-17 football team|under-17]], [[Germany national under-20 football team|under-20]] and [[Germany national under-21 football team|under-21]] levels.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/datencenter/personen/malik-tillman/spieler |title=Malik Tillman Spielerprofil |website=dfb.de |access-date=December 17, 2022}}</ref>

In May 2022, Tillman applied for a one-time switch to play for the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] national team.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayern-munich-youngster-malik-tillman-to-play-for-the-usa-20018 | title=Bayern Munich youngster Malik Tillman to play for the USA }}</ref> On May 31, the switch was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/united-states-usa/story/4678369/bayern-munichs-malik-tillman-cleared-to-represent-usmnt-after-fifa-approves-switch-from-germany | title=Bayern's Tillman cleared to represent USMNT | date=May 31, 2022 }}</ref> The next day, he made his senior debut for the United States in a 3–0 win in a friendly match against [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/joe-scally-and-malik-tillman-make-usmnt-debuts-in-morocco-friendly-20166 |title=Joe Scally and Malik Tillman make USMNT debuts in Morocco friendly |website=Bundesliga |date=June 1, 2022 }}</ref>

Tillman scored his first two goals for the United States on June 15, 2025 during the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup]] against [[Trinidad and Tobago national football team|Trinidad and Tobago]], and one week later he scored against [[Haiti national football team|Haiti]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-03-08 |title=Gold Cup Schedule & Results |url=https://www.concacaf.com/en/gold-cup/matches/ |access-date=2025-09-14 |website=Gold Cup |language=en}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Tillman is a dual national of the United States and Germany due to his father being American and his mother German. He has an older brother, [[Timothy Tillman|Timothy]], who currently plays professionally with [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Los Angeles FC]]. Both brothers played for the [[SpVgg Greuther Fürth|Greuther Fürth]] and [[FC Bayern Munich Junior Team|Bayern Munich]] academies.<ref name="Tillman"/>

